
git init -  Creates new repository

git status -  Displays the state of the repository

git add <filename> -  Will add the specified file
or
git add . -  Will add all the files

git commit -m "<Any message>" -  records the changes into repository with message

git remote add origin githubUrl -  To get git URL for the remote repository and add credentials if needed

  git config --global user.email "<github@email.com>" - To set the global email
  git config --global user.name "<Github username>" - To set the global username
  - Perform above two to avoid re-entering the credentails
  
git push -u origin master -  Push changes into the master branch within the repository

git log -  to check the logs/history

git --help -  For help 


